parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the ABS can cause the brakes to malfunction, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The ABS light comes on
the brakes feel soft or spongy
the brakes fail to engage
the vehicle continues to move despite pressing the brake pedal
the brakes suddenly release
and the vehicle vibrates violently when turning.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the brake hose can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake hose ruptures
the brake fluid leaks
the brakes fail to engage
the vehicle continues to move despite pressing the brake pedal
and the brake pedal feels soft or spongy.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the master cylinder can cause the brakes to fail, leading to loss of control, accidents, and potential injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The brake pedal feels soft or spongy
the brakes fail to engage
the vehicle continues to move despite pressing the brake pedal
and the brake fluid leaks.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the seat belt retractor can cause the seat belt to become loose or stuck, compromising the safety of the occupant and increasing the risk of injury or fatality in the event of an accident.
symptoms: The seat belt will not return into the retractor
leaving the occupant without any restraint; the seat belt will not release
making it unusable; the seat belt lies slack and doesn't retract back into the belt holder; the seat belt retractor gets tangled up; the seat belt has no pressure
force
or protection and hangs loose.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the driver's seat can cause the seat to collapse or break, leading to a loss of control while driving, which can result in accidents or injuries.
symptoms: The driver's seat breaks or collapses
the seat back falls backward
the seat anchor or bracket breaks
the seat housing breaks
the seat attachment disconnects
the seat comes off the track
the seat recliner mechanism slips backward.
